#5652
Outside the Afterlife~
During the day the building to the north appears to be a mundane
warehouse.  The only indication that it might be something else is the
framework for a large neon sign.  At night that sign lights up in meter tall
lettering that shifts in color from deep blue to yellow to a bright red and
then back again.  These letters spell out in a crisp designer font
"Afterlife".  When the sign is activated there is often a long line of
people spilling out onto the sidewalk.  At night men and women que in front
of the large double doors of the Afterlife.  It is a strange mix of rubber
corsets & piercings, glow sticks & baggy pants, and designer suits & Louis
Vuitton bags.  These three separate groups do the best they can to ignore
the others' presence.  Above the crowd a gangly man stands like some carnie
from hell.  He seems far too tall, made taller by his top hat and cane.  His
skin is stretched over his frame tightly, giving him more than a passing
resemblance to a skeleton.  He calls out to passers by, "Come one Come all
to the Afterlife!"  Two huge bouncers stand behind him, checking Ids and
keeping the crowd under control with their menacing glances.  The carnie
himself seems to be the one who picks who gets into the club and who
doesn't, blessing lucky people in the line with a nod and a gesture of his
silver-tipped cane.  
~
